    "body": "Ok, so the error is that you discriminate based on `totalSupply`, but `totalSupply` just gives you what is currently minted, not the cap.\r\n\r\nYour total supply starts out at `1e18`, so what you probably want is either to set the initial balance to 0, or change your fuzz test to something like:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n    function testMintFuzz(uint256 t) public {\r\n        if(t > type(uint256).max - 1e18) {\r\n            // totalSupply would overflow here\r\n            vm.expectRevert(stdError.arithmeticError);\r\n        }\r\n        m20.mint(msg.sender, t);\r\n        assertLt(t,m20.totalSupply());\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe reason you started getting these overflows *before* adding `vm.expectRevert` is because the fuzzer would give you a `t` so big that `t + initialBalance` was larger than `uint256`.\r\n\r\nThe reason your tests fail now *after* adding `vm.expectRevert` is because the fuzzer is giving you values for `t` that do *not* overflow.",
